Keep track of market trend and competitors’ activities;
Project document administration;

Requirements:

University real estate / sustainability studies / Environmental Science or related discipline;
2-5 years of market research experiences who should have strong analytical skills with experience in conducting reports and presentation.
Strong project management skills and attention to detail;

We offer competitive remuneration package to the right candidates. Interested parties, please submit your resume (in both English and Chinese), with stating current and expected salary, availability, contact phone number by APPLY NOW.

All applications and personal information collected will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for the purpose of recruitment and selection. The information collected will be accessed by our authorized personnel only. Unsuccessful applications will be retained for six months of possible future job matching, and will be destroyed after the expiry of six months.

The candidate will be responsible to drive various corporate sustainability initiatives across the Group. In this regard, the incumbent is required to:

Support and drive sustainability development and performance across the Group;
Collaborate with external parties and subsidiaries to develop and prepare sustainability reports;
Coordinate group-wide Environmental Management Committee;
Work with various benchmarking organisations to report and raise awareness of the Group’s sustainability performance;
Promote and engage stakeholders on sustainability through events and programmes, including sustainability marketing / promotional campaigns; and

Perform other duties as assigned by the supervisor.

Requirements


Bachelor and above degree holder in Environmental Science/ Management or related discipline;
At least 8 years’ relevant hands-on experience in corporate sustainability, including but not limited to reporting, data management etc;
Solid understanding of HKEX ESG disclosure requirements and GRI reporting standards;
Experience in organizing sustainability awareness programs and campaigns;
Strong business acumen to drive sustainability in commercial setting;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, including command of written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin; and
Entrepreneurial mindset, results-driven, mature, organized and meticulous.
We offer competitive salary and package for the right candidate. Interested parties please click "Apply Now" below to submit your application expected salary and availability.


Visit our website at www.nws.com.hk.
