Responsibilities

Plans projects and carries out chemical analysis to ensure work conforms to standard operating procedures and is completed accurately and in a timely manner;
Directs training of chemists and technicians on performing routine analysis according to standard operating procedures and QA/QC SDPs;
Modifies, evaluates and verifies analytical methods and procedures required for analytical testing;
Assists in reviewing logbooks to ensure QA/QC standards are met and applies safety rules and adheres to general conduct regulations in handling laboratory materials and equipment;
Arranges for removal of waste material generated by laboratory work in area of responsibility.

Requirements


Bachelor's Degree in basic science with minimum 2 years applicable experience or equivalent;
Must be able to apply analytical chemistry methods and techniques in working laboratory situation and participate actively in laboratory problem solving and production.  Previous experience on modern instruments and organic chemistry is required;
Sound background of applying QA/QC standards to analytical laboratory is an advantage;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese.

We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidates. Interested candidates are invited to send detailed resume with Current & Expected Salary and Availability to the Human Resources Department by clicking the “APPLY NOW” button. 

Ecospace Limited is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes applicants from all qualified candidates. The information provided will be treated in strict confidence and be used only for consideration of your application for relevant / similar posts within the Veolia Group.
All personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 24 months from the date of application.

Job responsibilities:

