To coordinate the planning, content development, liaison, promotion and implementation of educational mass programmes, events and activities related to environmental protection and waste management;
To coordinate the design and production of the publicity and education materials, and the management of social media platforms;
To engage and liaise with stakeholders in the communities to facilitate the promotion and implementation of the programmes / events / activities;
To supervise junior and part-time staff;
To perform other tasks pertaining to the work as assigned.

Working Hours: 45 hours per week and work on weekend when necessary   
Working Location:  Shatin District and Sai Kung District  

Please send your application letter quoting our job reference code together with a full resume, available date, last and expected salary by post to the Human Resources Department at 10/F, 3 Tsui Ping Road, Kwun Tong, Kowloon or by email via "Apply Now".
