Support production of corporate collaterals, including investor presentation, annual/interim results, press releases, etc. and perform other projects and duties as assigned;
Assist with media related matters including press release drafting, event on-site liaison, post event exposure analysis and peers analysis etc.;
Assist in collecting, calculating and managing ESG data for production of a bi-lingual ESG report, from cross-departmental liaison to content editing and publishing, follow with multi-platform promotions;
Support application of corporate awards and ESG-related submissions, including but not limited to Hang Seng sustainability index, Dow Jones Sustainability Index and GRESB to promote the Company’s reputation and ESG initiatives;
Assist in planning and organizing various Corporate Communications activities/events, including general meetings, results announcements; attend industry seminars/conferences;
Conduct bilingual translation/proof-reading, work with internal staff and external designers on photo selection, caption editing and layout design.

Requirements:

Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Communications, Translations, Environmental Science or related discipline;
2-3 years’ work relevant experience gained in PR agencies or property company preferred;
Relevant coursework in sustainability and communications preferred;
Strong communicator with good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (Putonghua) is a MUST;
Proficiency in PPT, MS office and Chinese word processing;
Initiative, analytical, sociable, presentable with good communication skills (being a good coordinator and organizer);
Strong project management skills and attention to detail;
Dedicated, self-motivated, able to work under pressure and deadline;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior Officer.

