Established in 2009, Hong Kong Green Building Council (“the Council”) is the leading body, co-founded by four major construction industry and environmental organisations, driving the market transformation towards green and sustainable buildings in Hong Kong through engagement with the industry, the government and broader community.

HKGBC is expanding its secretariat team in line with its positioning as Hong Kong's leading member-based body dedicated to green building development, with opening for the post of Executive II – Green Labelling:

Job Description

The role supports Assistant Manager to administer BEAM Plus scheme with a focus on promotion and training.

Assist to handle publicity events/campaigns on BEAM Plus;
Assist to prepare marketing collateral and communication materials related to BEAM Plus;
Handle event logistics such as training events, engagement events, annual BEAM Plus certification ceremony, BEAM Plus new scheme launching ceremonies, etc.;
Assist to handle BEAM Plus certification matters and perform related procurement processes such as ordering of plaques and trophies;
Maintain websites related to BEAM Plus such as BEAM Plus on-line exhibition website, BEAM Plus Existing Buildings resource website;
Assist to maintain register of BEAM practitioners and related training records;
Perform miscellaneous tasks such as data analysis and secretariat duties for committees;
Any other duties as assigned by supervisors.

Requirements:


A good university degree, preferably in communication, marketing or environmental field;
Fluent written and spoken English and Chinese, Level 4 or above in English and Chinese in the Hong Kong Diploma of Secondary Education (DSE) Examination or equivalent are preferred;
1 to 2 years’ working experience in promotion and/or training;
Be outgoing and proactive, with a strong drive to learn new skills and a passion to work in the field of green building or environmental protection;
Sound knowledge in Microsoft Office; and
Prior knowledge in design software like Adobe Illustrator and website management would be an asset.

How to Apply

The Council is an equal opportunity employer and offers attractive career prospects and remuneration to our staff. Recruitment will be initially under contract terms of two years with the possibility of converting to a permanent post. Interested applicants please apply by sending full resume with date of availability, present and expected salary, contact telephone number, as well as results of public examinations to the Executive Director, Hong Kong Green Building Council via e-mail careers @ hkgbc.org.hk, or by post to 1/F, Jockey Club Environmental Building, 77 Tat Chee Avenue, Kowloon Tong, Hong Kong. Please state the position you want to apply for on the envelope.

(N.B. Application with incomplete information as requested above may not be considered.)

Applicants who do not receive a response within six weeks from the date of this advertisement may consider their applications filed for future reference. Personal data will be used strictly for recruitment related purposes only and retained for no more than six months.

